LEGENDARY.Definition: very famous and admired or spoken about

STAND-UP.Definition: performed by a single person telling jokes and funny stories on stage

COMEDIAN.Definition: a person whose job is to make people laugh by telling jokes and funny stories or by copying the behavior or speech of famous people

HILARIOUS.Definition: extremely funny and causing a lot of laughter

PSYCHEDELIC.Definition: (of a drug) causing effects on the mind, such as feelings of deep understanding or unusually strong experiences of color, sound, taste, and touch

CRISP.Definition: a crisp way of speaking, writing, or behaving is quick, confident, and effective

PLANNED MY WHOLE DAY OUT.Definition: to think about and decide what you are going to do or how you are going to do something

SO FAR, SO GOOD.Definition: used to say that something (such as a project or an activity) has proceeded well or without problems up to the present

SMACK.Definition: to close and open (lips) noisily and often in rapid succession especially in eating

HIGH.Definition: intoxicated by or as if by a drug or alcohol

FREAKED OUT.Definition: to trouble the mind of; to make uneasy

CALM DOWN.Definition: to stop feeling upset, angry, or excited, or to stop someone feeling this way

COULDN'T TAKE IT.Definition: to not be able to deal with an unpleasant situation

HANDFUL.Definition: an amount of something that can be held in one hand

OPENED UP.Definition: to spread out or come into view

ANYWAY.Definition: in conversation, anyway is also used to change the subject, return to an earlier subject, or get to the most interesting point

TRIPPIN.Definition: an experience in which someone sees, hears, or feels things that do not exist as a result of taking an illegal drug

SOBER UP.Definition: to become sober or less drunk or to make (a drunk person) sober or less drunk

BLOCK.Definition: the distance along a street from where one road crosses it to the place where the next road crosses it, or one part of a street like this, especially in a town or city

FUCKED UP.Definition: to damage, harm, or upset someone or something, or to do something very badly

GODDAMN.Definition: used to emphasize or express annoyance with someone or something

INTERRUPT.Definition: to stop someone from speaking by saying or doing something, or to cause an activity or event to stop briefly

PEAK.Definition: the highest, strongest, or best point, value, or level of skill

COLLOQUIAL.Definition: (of words and expressions) informal and more suitable for use in speech than in writing

IMPLY.Definition: to communicate an idea or feeling without saying it directly

SAME EXACT.Definition: used as a more forceful way to say 'same'

ENDURE.Definition: to suffer something difficult, unpleasant, or painful

TOLERATE.Definition: to accept behavior and beliefs that are different from your own, although you might not agree with or approve of them

CRITICAL.Definition: saying that someone or something is bad or wrong

HARSH.Definition: unpleasant, unkind, cruel, or more severe than is necessary

ABUSIVE.Definition: treating someone badly or cruelly, esp. physically

PROPEL.Definition: to push or move something somewhere, often with a lot of force

INTOXICATED.Definition: having lost some control of your actions or behavior under the influence of alcohol or another drug
